H0.text: The third trimester is the period during a human pregnancy that exhibits the greatest growth of the fetus and culminates in labor and delivery.

H1.text: Fourth trimester is the period during a human pregnancy that exhibits the greatest growth of the fetus and culminates in labor and delivery.

H2.text: The first trimester is the trimester during a human pregnancy that exhibits the greatest growth of the fetus and culminates in labor and delivery.

H3.text: Second trimester is the trimester during human pregnancy that exhibits the greatest growth of the fetus and culminates in labor and delivery.

A4.text: Trimester (pregnancy) in humans, where the time of pregnancy is divided into three terms of 13 weeks to refer to the fetus's development

A5.text: Most weight gain takes place during the third trimester.

A6.text: Head engagement occurs as the fetal head descends into a cephalic presentation during the third trimester.
